\ Superinstructions: vv = two variable operands, v = one, then f + op.
\ All are compile-only immediate words that read variable names that follow.

variable a  20.0 to a
variable b  5.0 to b
variable c  2.0 to c

\ vvf+ vvf- vvf* vvf/ : ( -- A op B )
: s+ vvf+ a b ;   s+ . cr            \ 25
: s- vvf- a b ;   s- . cr            \ 15
: s* vvf* a b ;   s* . cr            \ 100
: s/ vvf/ a b ;   s/ . cr            \ 4

\ vfsq : ( -- A*A )
: ssq vfsq a ;   ssq . cr            \ 400

\ vvf*- : ( a -- C2 - a*A )  here a comes from the stack, A and C2 inline
\   C vvf*- A B  ->  B - C*A  =  5 - 2*20  =  -35
: sfms c vvf*- a b ;   sfms . cr     \ -35

\ vvf*+ : ( a -- a*A + C2 )
\   C vvf*+ A B  ->  C*A + B  =  2*20 + 5  =  45
: sfma c vvf*+ a b ;   sfma . cr     \ 45

\ composition: (A-B) squared via a temp
variable t1
: combo
  vvf- a b to t1       \ T1 = 20 - 5 = 15
  vfsq t1 ;            \ 15*15 = 225
combo . cr                           \ 225

\ fractional values
variable p  0.5 to p
variable q  0.25 to q
: sfrac vvf+ p q ;   sfrac . cr      \ 0.75
: sfracsq vfsq p ;   sfracsq . cr    \ 0.25

\ unary ops: one inline variable applied to the stack value.
\   vf+ X ( a -- a + X )   vf- X ( a -- a - X )
\   vf* X ( a -- a * X )   vf/ X ( a -- a / X )
: u+ vf+ b ;   100 u+ . cr           \ 105
: u- vf- b ;   100 u- . cr           \ 95
: u* vf* b ;   100 u* . cr           \ 500
: u/ vf/ b ;   100 u/ . cr           \ 20

\ unary order: subtract/divide use the stack value as the left operand
: uorder 7 vf- c ;   uorder . cr     \ 7 - 2 = 5

\ chains with the binary forms
: uchain vvf* a b  vf+ c ;   uchain . cr   \ 20*5 + 2 = 102

clear
\ Auto-fusion: idiomatic float ops over variables are fused to superwords
\ at compile time. Results must equal the unfused forms, and fusion inside
\ control flow must preserve branch offsets.

variable a  3.0 to a
variable b  4.0 to b

\ two variables + binop -> vvf
: t1 a b f- ;   t1 . cr          \ -1
: t2 a b f* ;   t2 . cr          \ 12

\ stack value + one variable -> vf
: t3 10.0 a f- ;   t3 . cr       \ 7
: t4 10.0 a f/ ;   t4 . cr       \ 3.33333

\ unary function of one variable -> vfn
: t5 a sq ;     t5 . cr          \ 9
: t6 b sqrt ;   t6 . cr          \ 2

\ stack value + two variables, fused multiply -> vvf*- / vvf*+
\ f*- is ( a b c -- c - a*b ),  f*+ is ( a b c -- a*b + c )
: t7 5.0 a b f*- ;   t7 . cr     \ 4 - 5*3 = -11
: t8 5.0 a b f*+ ;   t8 . cr     \ 5*3 + 4 = 19

\ fusion inside both arms of if/else
: branchy 0 > if a b f* else a b f+ then ;
1 branchy . cr                   \ 12
0 branchy . cr                   \ 7

\ fusion inside a begin/until loop body
variable acc
variable i
: loopy
  0.0 to acc  0.0 to i
  begin  a b f* acc f+ to acc  i 1+ to i  i 3.0 = until
  acc ;
loopy . cr                       \ 36

\ a non-fusing case for contrast: locals, not variables
: withlocal | x y | a to x  b to y  x y f- ;   withlocal . cr   \ -1

clear
\ Store fusion: <superword> to <var> folds into one op that writes the
\ variable directly (verified via see-compiled separately; here we check
\ the results are correct).

variable a  10.0 to a
variable b  3.0 to b
variable c

\ two-var binary -> vvf*!
: s1 a b f- to c ;   s1 c . cr      \ 7
: s2 a b f* to c ;   s2 c . cr      \ 30
: s3 a b f+ to c ;   s3 c . cr      \ 13
: s4 a b f/ to c ;   s4 c . cr      \ 3.33333

\ stack value + one var -> vf*!
: s5 100.0 a f- to c ;   s5 c . cr  \ 100 - 10 = 90

\ unary function -> vfn!
: s6 a sq to c ;       s6 c . cr    \ 100
: s7 a negate to c ;   s7 c . cr    \ -10

\ fused multiply -> vvf*-! / vvf*+!  (f*- is c - a*b, f*+ is a*b + c)
: s8 5.0 a b f*- to c ;   s8 c . cr  \ 3 - 5*10 = -47
: s9 5.0 a b f*+ to c ;   s9 c . cr  \ 5*10 + 3 = 53

\ store target same as a source (the nbody writeback pattern): C = A * C
2.0 to c
: s10 a c f* to c ;   s10 c . cr     \ 10 * 2 = 20 (reads old C before writing)

clear
\ Fusion floor: a local loaded before `begin` and one loaded after it must not
\ fuse across the loop-back target. Before the floor, `start begin step f+` fused
\ start+step into a single (ll+0) straddling the begin point, so the loop's
\ back-branch landed inside that op and the word crashed silently. It must run
\ the loop (i: 5..1) and leave 3 + 4*5 = 23.
: floor-test | start step i |
  3.0 to start  4.0 to step  5.0 to i
  start begin step f+ i 1.0 f- to i i 0.0 f> 0= until ;
floor-test . cr

\ Store-fusion floor: `to <var>` right after a control-flow boundary must not
\ fuse a var-op that sits below the boundary into a store variant. `then` had
\ patched the branch to the position where `to` compiles; fusing rewound `here`
\ below it, so the branch landed inside the rewritten store op. Both arms end in
\ a var-op, so `to c` sits just after `then`; each path must reach it intact.
7.0 to a  2.0 to b
: store-floor 0= if vvf* a b else vvf+ a b then to c ;
0 store-floor c . cr                 \ flag 0 -> vvf* -> 14
1 store-floor c . cr                 \ flag 1 -> vvf+ -> 9
